        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 6:36PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 636 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Nutt to 9 miles northeast of Akela to 12
miles west of Afton. Movement was northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hatch, Nutt, Rincon, Salem, Garfield, Uvas Valley, Corralitos, Las
Cruces West Mesa, Southern New Mexico State Fairgrounds, Aden Crater,
Magdalena Peak, and Macho Springs.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 10 in New Mexico between mile markers 112 and 133.
Interstate 25 in New Mexico between mile markers 38 and 47.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
